Class Terminal

  • java.lang.Object
    • sudokuGame.TerminalOrPrimitive
      • sudokuGame.Terminal
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Terminal
extends TerminalOrPrimitive
    Terminal class is representing the the terminal function (terminal node) in our Tree-based Genetic Programing. And we use this class as a generic T value in the Node class.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Abedalrhman Nsasra

    • Constructor Detail

      • Terminal

        public Terminal(java.lang.String operationName)
        Constructor that initialize Terminal instance, and always determine "Terminal" String as nodeType. and set operationName parameter as the function that should run in the Terminal instance in our Tree-based Genetic Programing
        Parameters:
        operationName - is a String that determine the function operation in the Terminal Node in our Tree-based Genetic Programing. The function that the Terminal instance could operate (run): countEmptyCellInRow, countEmptyCellInCol, countEmptyCellInSquare, numOfOptionsInCell, numOfOptionsToAppearInBoard, countEmptyCellsInRowsContainsNum, countEmptyCellsInColsContainsNum, countEmptyCellsInSquareContainsNum, countEmptyCellsInRows_ThatNotContainsNum, countEmptyCellsInCols_ThatNotContainsNum, countEmptyCellsInSquare_ThatNotContainsNum. and of course the list can be extended if you want to. Notice: that Terminal can only operate and only one function.

      • run

        double run(int row,
           int col,
           int key,
           int[][] board,
           java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Double>[][] gradeBoard)
        Call the method with name operationName with the parameters that received, and return the number that method is returned. The number is represent how much good is the parameter key as a solution in board[row,col], smaller is better, we could choose the the opposite, it will NOT change the solution. Notice: that all return numbers will returned to parent node in the tree (it should be Primitive type).
        Specified by:
        run in class TerminalOrPrimitive
        Parameters:
        row - The index of the row in the Sudoku board.
        col - The index of the column in the Sudoku board.
        key - One of the options (number 1-9) that can be inserted in [row,col] in the board without conflict.
        board - Reference to the Sudoku board matrix with size 9x9, we don't copy the board it's just a reference.
        gradeBoard - Reference to matrix of hash tables that represent in every index in the matrix which numbers can be inserted without conflict as a keys in the hash table and grade as a value for every key that represent how good this option as solution, we choose smaller grade is better but you could choose larger is better, it will not change the solution.
        Returns:
        the number that the method with name operationName is returned.
        See Also:
        run(int, int, int, int[][], Hashtable[][]), Primitive.run(int, int, int, int[][], Hashtable[][])

      • countEmptyCellInSquare

        private int countEmptyCellInSquare(int row,
                                   int col,
                                   int[][] board)
        This method calculate the range of the gaven index of a square and count the empty cell in that square. For example: in 9x9 sudoku board, if the method receive [row=0, col=0] it will count the empty indexes, in the range [0-2,0,2]. And another example if it receive [row= 3, col=3] it will count the empty indexes, in the range [3-5,3-5]. So we determine the range and count the empty in that range (square), Notice that the code written to support any sudoku with length NxN, when sqrt(N) is a natural number. squareLength - it's the length of the square, in 9x9 sudoku the squareLength is 3, in in 16x16 sudoku the squareLength is 4. we use it for a general NxN sudoku.
        Parameters:
        row - is the row index that exist in a square.
        col - is the column index that exist in a square.
        board - is 2D array that represent the sudoku board.
        Returns:
        the empty cells in the square that comprehensive the gaven index [row,col], [rowStartIndex, colStartIndex] to [rowStartIndex+squareLength, colStartIndex+squareLength].
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - if the board dimensions NxN is NOT quadratic: the sqrt(N) is NOT natural number.

      • numOfOptionsInCell

        private int numOfOptionsInCell(int row,
                               int col,
                               java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Double>[][] gradeboard)
        This method receive index (row,col) in the sudoku board and count the legal options (without conflict) that can be inserted in that index.
        Parameters:
        row - is the row index that we want check.
        col - is the column index that we want check.
        gradeboard - a matrix of hash tables, that save in every index the legal options that can be inserted (without conflict) in that index as keys, and mapping a grade to that option that represent how much good that option as solution in that index. Note: The size of keys in any index is the number of the options (without conflict) in that index.
        Returns:
        the count of the options that can be inserted (without conflict) in in index [row, col].

      • numOfOptionsToAppearInBoard

        private int numOfOptionsToAppearInBoard(int key,
                                        int[][] board)
        In 9x9 sudoku every number can appear exactly 9 times, in NxN sudoku every number can appear exactly N times. So in this method we count the times that number "key" appear in the sudoku, and return the remaining times that can appear (N - appearTimes).
        Parameters:
        key - is a number (1 to 9 in 9x9 sudoku) or (1 to N in NxN sudoku) that can be solution in any cell.
        board - is 2D array that represent the sudoku board.
        Returns:
        the remaining times that the number "key" can appear in the sudoku.

      • countEmptyCellsInSquareContainsNum

        private int countEmptyCellsInSquareContainsNum(int key,
                                               int[][] board)
        This method scan all the nxn square in the board, if the square contain the "key" number, then the method count the empty cells in that square, and eventually return the sum of all empty cells in all square that contain key number as a solution. Important Note: if the sudoku dimensions is NxN then the square dimensions is nxn, when n=sqrt(N) and n is a neutral number. squareLength - it's the length of the square, in 9x9 sudoku the squareLength is 3, in in 16x16 sudoku the sizeOfSquare is 4. we use it for a general NxN sudoku.
        Parameters:
        key - is a number (1 to 9 in 9x9 sudoku) or (1 to N in NxN sudoku) that can be solution in any cell.
        board - is 2D array that represent the sudoku board.
        Returns:
        the empty cells in all squares that contain "key" number as a solution.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - if the board dimensions NxN is NOT quadratic: the sqrt(N) is NOT natural number.

      • existInSquare

        static boolean existInSquare(int row,
                             int col,
                             int num,
                             int[][] board)
        This method receive the index of cell [row, col] and check if the num is really exist in the square that comprehensive that index. For example in 9x9 sudoku, the square [0-2,0-2] is comprehensive the index [0,0]. Notice that the code written to support any sudoku with length NxN, when sqrt(N) is a natural number. squareLength - it's the length of the square, in 9x9 sudoku the squareLength is 3, in in 16x16 sudoku the squareLength is 4. we use it for a general NxN sudoku.
        Parameters:
        row - is the index of the row that we want to check if it contain num.
        col - is the index of the column that we want to check if it contain num.
        num - the number that we want to check if it's already exist in the square that comprehensive the index [row, col].
        board - is 2D array that represent the sudoku board.
        Returns:
        true if the number already exist in the range if the square that comprehensive [row, col], false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - if the board dimensions NxN is NOT quadratic: the sqrt(N) is NOT natural number.
